SIMPLE: recline
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Recline
<hw>Re*cline"</hw> <pr>(r⟦esl⟧*kl⟦imac⟧n")</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> <conjf>Reclined</conjf>
<pr>(r⟦esl⟧*kl⟦imac⟧nd")</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Reclining</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[L. <ets>reclinare</ets>; pref.
<ets>re-</ets> re- + <ets>clinare</ets> to lean, incline. See
<er>Incline</er>, <er>Lean</er> to incline.]</ety> <def>To cause or
permit to lean, incline, rest, etc.; to place in a recumbent position;
<as>as, to <ex>recline</ex> the head on the hand</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The mother⟦br⟧
<qex>Reclined</qex> her dying head upon his breast.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Recline</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Recline
<hw>Re*cline"</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To lean or
incline; <as>as, to <ex>recline</ex> against a wall</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To assume, or to be in, a recumbent position;
<as>as, to <ex>recline</ex> on a couch</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Recline</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Recline
<hw>Re*cline"</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>reclinis</ets>. See
<er>Recline</er>, <pos>v. t.</pos>]</ety> <def>Having a reclining
posture; leaning; reclining.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>They sat, <qex>recline</qex>⟦br⟧
On the soft downy bank, damasked with flowers.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Reclined</ent>⟦br⟧
